HOUSE BILL 825
J1, P1 6lr1508
By: Delegates Woods, Roberts, Bhandari, Coley, Cullison, Fair, Ghrist, Harrison,
Martinez, Patterson, Roberson, Sample–Hughes, Simmons, Stinnett,
Taveras, Taylor, and Toles
Introduced and read first time: February 4, 2026
Assigned to: Government, Labor, and Elections and Appropriations
A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Brain Health – Guidelines, Grant Fund, and Commemorative Month
3 (Tahjai’s Law)
4 FOR the purpose of requiring the Governor annually to proclaim the month of May to be
5 Brain Health and Chronic Headache Awareness Month; requiring the proclamation
6 to align with national Go Gray in May brain tumor awareness initiatives;
7 establishing the Maryland Brain Health Grant Fund as a special, nonlapsing fund;
8 requiring the Maryland Department of Health, in collaboration with certain entities,
9 to develop guidelines on brain health evaluations; requiring the Department to
10 develop recommendations on brain health screening intervals and insurance parity;
11 and generally relating to brain health.
12 BY renumbering
13 Article – General Provisions
14 Section 7–504 through 7–507
15 to be Section 7–505 through 7–508, respectively
16 Annotated Code of Maryland
17 (2019 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
18 BY adding to
19 Article – General Provisions
20 Section 7–504
21 Annotated Code of Maryland
22 (2019 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
23 BY adding to
24 Article – Health – General
EXPLANATION: CAPITALS INDICATE MATTER ADDED TO EXISTING LAW.
