2 HOUSE BILL 825
1 Section 20–2501 and 20–2502 to be under the new subtitle “Subtitle 25. Brain
2 Health”; and 24–2801 and 24–2802 to be under the new subtitle “Subtitle 28.
3 Maryland Brain Health Grant Fund”
4 Annotated Code of Maryland
5 (2023 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
6 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
7 That Section(s) 7–504 through 7–507 of Article – General Provisions of the Annotated Code
8 of Maryland be renumbered to be Section(s) 7–505 through 7–508, respectively.
9 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That the Laws of Maryland read
10 as follows:
11 Article – General Provisions
12 7–504.
13 (A) THE GOVERNOR ANNUALLY SHALL PROCLAIM THE MONTH OF MAY AS
14 BRAIN HEALTH AND CHRONIC HEADACHE AWARENESS MONTH.
15 (B) THE PROCLAMATION SHALL ALIGN WITH NATIONAL GO GRAY IN MAY
16 BRAIN TUMOR AWARENESS INITIATIVES.
17 Article – Health – General
18 SUBTITLE 25. BRAIN HEALTH.
19 20–2501.
20 (A) (1) THE DEPARTMENT, IN COLLABORATION WITH HEALTH CARE
21 PRACTITIONERS, PAYORS, AND OTHER STAKEHOLDERS, SHALL DEVELOP
22 GUIDELINES THAT PROMOTE THE INCORPORATION OF A RISK–BASED BRAIN
23 HEALTH EVALUATION INTO A ROUTINE PHYSICAL EXAMINATION AND WELLNESS
24 VISIT.
25 (2) AN EVALUATION INCLUDED IN THE GUIDELINES MAY INCLUDE:
26 (I) A NEUROLOGICAL ASSESSMENT;
27 (II) AN EVIDENCE–BASED DECISION TOOL; AND
28 (III) A REFERRAL PROTOCOL FOR NONINVASIVE IMAGING.
29 (B) THE DEPARTMENT SHALL DEVELOP RECOMMENDATIONS:

HOUSE BILL 825 3
1 (1) ESTABLISHING SCREENING INTERVALS FOR BRAIN HEALTH
2 EVALUATIONS; AND
3 (2) PROMOTING INSURANCE COVERAGE PARITY FOR MEDICALLY
4 NECESSARY BRAIN HEALTH DIAGNOSTIC TOOLS.
5 20–2502.
6 ON OR BEFORE DECEMBER 1 EACH YEAR BEGINNING IN 2026, THE
7 DEPARTMENT SHALL SUBMIT TO THE GOVERNOR AND, IN ACCORDANCE WITH §
8 2–1257 OF THE STATE GOVERNMENT ARTICLE, THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY A REPORT
9 THAT INCLUDES STATEWIDE DATA FOR THE IMMEDIATELY PRECEDING FISCAL YEAR
10 ON:
11 (1) BRAIN TUMOR AND CHRONIC HEADACHE PREVALENCE;
12 (2) EMERGENCY DEPARTMENT VISITS RELATED TO BRAIN TUMORS
13 AND CHRONIC HEADACHES;
14 (3) ACCESS TO DIAGNOSTIC BRAIN IMAGING; AND
15 (4) BARRIERS TO BRAIN HEALTH–RELATED CARE.
16 SUBTITLE 28. MARYLAND BRAIN HEALTH GRANT FUND.
17 24–2801.
18 (A) IN THIS SUBTITLE THE FOLLOWING WORDS HAVE THE MEANINGS
19 INDICATED.
20 (B) “BRAIN HEALTH SERVICES” INCLUDES PREVENTION, EVALUATION,
21 DIAGNOSIS, TREATMENT, THERAPY, EDUCATION, AND SUPPORT RELATED TO:
22 (1) A BRAIN TUMOR;
23 (2) A CHRONIC HEADACHE;
24 (3) A MIGRAINE;
25 (4) TRAUMATIC BRAIN INJURY;
26 (5) A CEREBROVASCULAR CONDITION; AND

4 HOUSE BILL 825
1 (6) ANY OTHER NEUROLOGICAL PAIN DISORDER.
2 (C) “FUND” MEANS THE MARYLAND BRAIN HEALTH GRANT FUND.
3 24–2802.
4 (A) THERE IS A MARYLAND BRAIN HEALTH GRANT FUND.
5 (B) THE PURPOSE OF THE FUND IS TO PROVIDE GRANTS TO NONPROFIT
6 ORGANIZATIONS, HEALTH CARE PROVIDERS, LOCAL HEALTH DEPARTMENTS, AND
7 COMMUNITY–BASED PROGRAMS TO SUPPORT BRAIN HEALTH AWARENESS, BRAIN
8 HEALTH SCREENING, BRAIN ILLNESS PREVENTION, AND BRAIN HEALTH SERVICES.
9 (C) THE DEPARTMENT SHALL ADMINISTER THE FUND.
10 (D) (1) THE FUND IS A SPECIAL, NONLAPSING FUND THAT IS NOT
11 SUBJECT TO § 7–302 OF THE STATE FINANCE AND PROCUREMENT ARTICLE.
12 (2) THE STATE TREASURER SHALL HOLD THE FUND SEPARATELY,
13 AND THE COMPTROLLER SHALL ACCOUNT FOR THE FUND.
14 (E) THE FUND CONSISTS OF:
15 (1) MONEY APPROPRIATED IN THE STATE BUDGET TO THE FUND;
16 AND
17 (2) ANY OTHER MONEY FROM ANY OTHER SOURCE ACCEPTED FOR
18 THE BENEFIT OF THE FUND.
19 (F) (1) THE FUND MAY BE USED ONLY FOR:
20 (I) PROVIDING GRANTS TO NONPROFIT ORGANIZATIONS,
21 HEALTH CARE PROVIDERS, LOCAL HEALTH DEPARTMENTS, AND
22 COMMUNITY–BASED PROGRAMS TO SUPPORT:
23 1. BRAIN HEALTH AWARENESS ACTIVITIES;
24 2. BRAIN HEALTH SCREENING SERVICES;
25 3. BRAIN ILLNESS PREVENTION ACTIVITIES; AND
26 4. BRAIN HEALTH SERVICES;

HOUSE BILL 825 5
1 (II) ADMINISTRATIVE EXPENSES OF THE DEPARTMENT IN
2 ADMINISTERING THE FUND; AND
3 (III) ANY OTHER USE DETERMINED APPROPRIATE BY THE
4 DEPARTMENT AFTER THE CONSULTATION REQUIRED UNDER PARAGRAPH (2) OF
5 THIS SUBSECTION.
6 (2) THE DEPARTMENT SHALL CONSULT PERIODICALLY WITH THE
7 SOLID FOUNDATION, INC., RELEVANT CLINICAL EXPERTS, AND PATIENT ADVOCACY
8 GROUPS REGARDING THE USE OF THE FUND.
9 (G) (1) THE STATE TREASURER SHALL INVEST THE MONEY OF THE FUND
10 IN THE SAME MANNER AS OTHER STATE MONEY MAY BE INVESTED.
11 (2) ANY INTEREST EARNINGS OF THE FUND SHALL BE CREDITED TO
12 THE GENERAL FUND OF THE STATE.
13 (H) EXPENDITURES FROM THE FUND MAY BE MADE ONLY IN ACCORDANCE
14 WITH THE STATE BUDGET.
15 (I) THE DEPARTMENT SHALL:
16 (1) ESTABLISH TRANSPARENT CRITERIA FOR AWARDING GRANTS
17 FROM THE FUND;
18 (2) PRIORITIZE PROVIDING GRANTS FROM THE FUND TO SUPPORT
19 ACTIVITIES IN UNDERSERVED COMMUNITIES; AND
20 (3) ENSURE EQUITABLE GEOGRAPHIC DISTRIBUTION OF GRANTS
21 FROM THE FUND THROUGHOUT THE STATE.
22 (J) ON OR BEFORE DECEMBER 1 EACH YEAR BEGINNING IN 2026, THE
23 DEPARTMENT SHALL SUBMIT TO THE GOVERNOR AND, IN ACCORDANCE WITH
24 § 2–1257 OF THE STATE GOVERNMENT ARTICLE, THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY A
25 REPORT ON THE USE OF THE FUND DURING THE IMMEDIATELY PRECEDING FISCAL
26 YEAR.
27 SECTION 3. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That, for fiscal year 2028, the
28 Governor shall include in the annual budget bill an appropriation in an amount of $500,000
29 to the Maryland Brain Health Grant Fund established under § 24–2802 of the Health –
30 General Article, as enacted by Section 2 of this Act.

6 HOUSE BILL 825
1 SECTION 4. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That, on or before January 1, 2027,
2 the Maryland Department of Health shall submit a report to the Governor and, in
3 accordance with § 2–1257 of the State Government Article, the General Assembly on:
4 (1) the guidelines developed under § 20–2501(a) of the Health – General
5 Article, as enacted by Section 2 of this Act; and
6 (2) any recommendations developed under § 20–2501(b) of the Health –
7 General Article, as enacted by Section 2 of this Act.
8 SECTION 5. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect July
9 1, 2026.

